        "The pressure is different from a3_s16. In a3_s16 the pressure was the pressure of a woman confirming a hypothesis. In this scene the pressure is the pressure of a woman who has stopped having hypotheses."

        nthought "Twelve beats."

        nthought "Twelve beats above baseline."

        nthought "I am not measuring. I am registering the measurement as it arrives. The measurement is an involuntary output of the old frame. The old frame is still producing outputs. I am letting the outputs arrive and letting them not become the scene."

        nthought "The scene is not about the measurements."

        nthought "The scene is about the hand."

        "She does not look at the screens."

        "She does not look at the secondary screens with the seven names, or at the primary screen with the failed model annotation, or at the blank NEW MODEL document with its cursor at the first line."

        "She looks at Aeron."

        n "Aeron."

        "One word."

        "The single deployment of the name in the scene. Not warm. Tactical. She is labeling a variable. The variable she is labeling is the variable she is about to use as an input the old frame cannot predict."

        n "I am using your name because the new frame uses the name. The new frame does not call you Commander. The new frame does not call you Glass. The new frame calls you by your name because the new frame is not going to be delicate about the inputs."

        nthought "I noticed I said that out loud. I am permitting myself to have said it out loud. The permitting is the becoming."

        a "Understood."

        "One word. He is not contributing content to the hour. He is confirming receipt of her labels. The confirmation is the most he needs to do in this register."

        # ========== PHASE 5 -- THE SCREENS STAY ON ==========

        # CAMERA: wide. The alcove at full luminance. Two figures at the
        # center. The screens all around them.

        "Noelle does not dim the screens."

        "In a3_s16 the screens stayed on as a statement of her intimacy with clarity. In this scene the screens stay on because dimming the screens would be a gesture toward comfort and the scene is not about comfort. The scene is about replacing a frame that failed with a frame that has not yet been built. The replacement cannot happen in the dark."

        "The seven names on the secondary screen are still visible."

        "The failed model annotation on the primary screen is still visible."

        "The blank NEW MODEL document's cursor is still blinking."

        "The alcove is working at full load."

        "The scene happens in the working load."

        # [INTIMATE CONTENT HERE]

    # ========== PHASE 6 -- AFTERCARE ==========

        # CAMERA: locked medium wide. Noelle back at her workstation chair.
        # The scene's time-jump is the camera's re-lock -- from the intimacy
