        "The stopping is the loudest sound in the alcove -- per the a3_s16 thesis, the silence when she stops typing is the loudest sound in the scene."

        "She is not looking at the scaffolding. Her hands are still on the keyboard, fingers curled over the home row, but she is not typing."

        "She speaks without turning."

        n "My doctrine did not fail because the doctrine was wrong."

        "Ten words."

        "She pauses."

        n "It failed because I was an analyst when I should have been a weapon."

        "Twelve words."

        "The two sentences are the scene's declaration. The declaration is the first sentence of the new frame. The scaffolding on the screen is the structural preparation. The declaration is the thing the structure is structured around."

