        a "What does being a weapon mean for you."

        "Seven words. The sentence is a question. The question is asked in the register of a commander asking a subordinate about the subordinate's operational specialization."

        "The register is not warm."

        "The register is correct."

        "Noelle does not turn to answer. Her hands are still on the keyboard. Her fingers are still on the home row."

        n "I am going to find out."

        "Six words."

        "The sentence is an answer and also a commitment. The commitment is to the process of discovering the content of the commitment. The analyst-frame would have required the content to be specified in advance. The weapon-frame does not require the content in advance. The weapon-frame requires only the declaration. The content will be discovered in the application of the declaration."

        n "Close the door on your way out."

        "Six more words."

        "The sentence is the indication Aeron was waiting for. The hour is complete. The alcove is Noelle's again. The weapon's new frame is going to be built in the alcove after Aeron leaves, and the building is going to happen in the register Aeron is not invited into."

